{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_107","type":"agent_message","text":"I updated the Scala 2.11.8 shard in three places: the library metadata at [reachability-metadata.json](/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge4/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2158-4ef82f88/metadata/org.scala-lang/scala-library/2.11.8/reachability-metadata.json:55), the test fixture config at [build.gradle](/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge4/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2158-4ef82f88/tests/src/org.scala-lang/scala-library/2.11.8/build.gradle:44), and test-only reflection metadata at [reachability-metadata.json](/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge4/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2158-4ef82f88/tests/src/org.scala-lang/scala-library/2.11.8/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json:1). That fixes the `sun.misc.Unsafe.theUnsafe` access for `LinkedTransferQueue` and the native common-pool worker factory setup.\n\nVerification is improved but not fully green. `nativeTest` now passes `ForkJoinPoolTest`, `LinkedTransferQueueTest`, `ListBufferTest`, `ListInnerSerializationProxyTest`, `TrieMapTest`, and `ClassManifestDeprecatedApisInnerclassTest`. The remaining failure is still `EnumerationTest.resolvesDeserializedValueToSingletonEnumerationInstance()`, with `MissingReflectionRegistrationError: Cannot reflectively invoke constructor 'public java.lang.Object()'` during `ObjectInputStream` deserialization of `scala.Enumeration$Val`.\n\nOne other constraint: the user-provided `generateMetadata` reproduction still fails earlier in this environment because `native-image-agent` cannot be loaded (`libnative-image-agent.so` not found), so I used `nativeTest` as the verification loop instead.\n\nIf you want, I can keep digging specifically into that last enum deserialization path; that’s the only blocker left."}}
